flowRoot.flowPara: Fetch stage sends PC to Instruction Memory and computes new PC as PC+1 (Instruction RAM is not 8 bits wide but 32 outputting in parallel)

Decode stage converts opcode to control signals for later stages (delayed by proper amount of registers). It also provides immediately to the register file the addresses of the needed data. If a jump is detected, the instruction being fetched is dumped (decode NOP instead) and previous PC and jump offset are passed to ALU for PC computation. Next instruction is also a NOP (waiting for PC being calculated). If the jump is a conditional branch condition is computed in ALU in parallel with target PC, then either computed PC or next PC or is selected depending on wether the condition is verified.
